  # Inflation
  blocks {
    title: "Inflation rate"
    description: "Inflation rates tell you how much consumer prices have increased over a specified period of time. It is like a speedometer for prices: high inflation means your money buys you less than before and low inflation means prices are steady and your money retains its value."

