### REMITTANCES ###
categories {
  title: "Remittances"
  description: "Remittances are money or goods that migrants send back to families and friends in origin countries. They are often the most direct and well-known link between migration and development, and can be a lifeline in times of crisis. The level of remittances to African countries can surpass the amount of funds received through official aid or foreign investments."

