### SPECIAL DRAWING RIGHTS ###
categories {
  title: "Special Drawing Rights"
  description: "Special Drawing Rights (SDRs) are a reserve asset issued by the International Monetary Fund (IMF) to all its members. They are not cash, but they can be traded for hard currency if countries need to use them. In times of crisis, SDRs can  provide a much needed injection of liquidity to shore up reserves, stabilise currencies, meet external debt obligations, or address other pressing needs.\n\nA country’s relative size in the global economy determines how much it receives — so richer countries get the lion’s share. The most recent SDR allocation equivalent to $650 billion took place in August 2021 to help countries respond to the COVID-19 pandemic."

